Reasoning: The paper deals with the resistance of a cryptosystem against correlation attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Fourier spectra and discrete Fourier transform (DFT) suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The study of correlation-immune functions over $\mathbb{F}_p$ involves algebraic structures and mathematical properties, which aligns with the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) as it deals with the complexity of correlation attacks on cryptosystems.
